OL,3,CCouncillors warn of abuse at public
OL,4,Cmeetings
OL,6,F"It does put you off. The negatives of
OL,7,Fthe abuse, which is online and in
OL,8,Fperson, will tip those decisions. It's
OL,9,Fcertainly not the career I thought it
OL,10,Fwould be and it is worrying the level
OL,11,Fof abuse that I've seen."
OL,13,FThe Convention of Scottish Local
OL,14,FAuthorities (COSLA), says, across
OL,15,FScotland, there's been a 'significant
OL,16,Fincrease' in abuse against councillors
OL,17,Fand it's putting people off standing
OL,18,Ffor election.
