OL,3,CCouncillors warn of abuse at public
OL,4,Cmeetings
OL,6,FCllr Shona Morrison, COSLA President,
OL,7,Fsaid: "We're seeing a real rise in
OL,8,Fabuse towards councillors, to elected
OL,9,Fmembers, to our officers in some
OL,10,Fcouncils as well. We've found it
OL,11,Freally worrying, in recent months and
OL,12,Fyears, the level of online abuse that
OL,13,Fso many of our women leaders
OL,14,Fspecifically are experiencing."
OL,16,FCouncillor Thomson added: "As things
OL,17,Fget tighter, as budgets get tighter, I
OL,18,Fthink it will get worse."
